    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="558" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                <head>No. 558.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">L. S. Sackville
                                    West</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6,
                                1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 14th
                            ultimo, inquiring whether it would be possible for this Government to
                            adopt any measures for preventing vessels sold to and owned by American
                            citizens from continuing <pb facs="0926" n="790" xml:id="pg_790"/> to
                            sail under the British flag, I hare the honor to inform you that the
                            Secretary of the Treasury, to whom the matter was referred, reports that
                            there does not seem to be any legislation of the United States bearing
                            upon the subject, and that in the absence of such legislation it would
                            not be practicable for the executive or judicial branch of this
                            Government to intervene with a view to the prevention of transactions of
                            the character mentioned in your note.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                                Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
